Proposed Amendments to the City of Toronto Municipal Code for increases to the Solid Waste Management Services (SWMS) rates and fees.
Notice is hereby given that City officials are recommending to Toronto City Council the enactment of a by-law, effective January 1, 2023, amending the City of Toronto Municipal Code Chapter 441, Fees and Charges, and any other necessary Municipal Code Chapters as may be required to increase the SWMS rates and fees by customer group as follows:

3.0% rate increase to properties that receive Multi-Residential Front End Container and Multi-Residential Curbside collection services;
3.0% rate increase to all Single Family Residential and Residential Units Above Commercial (RUAC) properties;
3.0% increase in bag tags and bin purchases; and
3.0% increase in Commercial; City Divisions, Agencies, Corporations and Schools.

As shown in Appendix A, the recommended interim increase in the Solid Waste Management Services 2023 rates and fee, effective January 1, 2023 are shown in the following link: https://www.toronto.ca/legdocs/mmis/2023/ex/bgrd/backgroundfile-230209.pdf
&nbsp;
